'''盧德國際機場掃射事件'''（{{lang-he|הטבח בנמל התעופה לוד}}；{{lang-ja|テルアビブ空港乱射事件}}）是指1972年5月30日所發生的一宗由[[解放巴勒斯坦人民陣線|解放巴勒斯坦人民陣線]]和3名[[日本赤軍|日本赤軍]]成員所策劃<ref>"The short-term impact of the Lod Airport massacre as a precursor to Munich..." Stephen Sloan, John C. Bersia, J. B. Hill. ''Terrorism: The Present Threat in Context'', Berg Publisher, 2006, p. 50. ISBN 1845203445</ref><ref>"Two years later, just before the Lod Airport massacre, authorities uncovered the bodies of 14 young men and women on remote Mount Haruna, 70 miles northwest of Tokyo." [http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,917724,00.html "Again the Red Army"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,917724,00.html |date=20130826005453 }}, ''[[Time_(magazine)|TIME]]'', August 18, 1975.</ref><ref>"Those named by Lebanese officials as having been arrested included at least three Red Army members who have been wanted for years by Japanese authorities, most notably Kozo Okamoto, 49, the only member of the attacking group who survived the Lod Airport massacre." [http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9D02E6DF1F3FF93AA25751C0A961958260 "Lebanon Seizes Japanese Radicals Sought in Terror Attacks"], ''[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]'', February 19, 1997.</ref><ref>"They were responsible for the Lod Airport massacre in Israel in 1972, which was committed on behalf of the PFLP." Jeffrey D. Simon, ''The Terrorist Trap: America's Experience with Terrorism'', Indiana University Press, p. 324. ISBN 0253214777</ref>並在[[盧德國際機場|盧德國際機場]]（現改名為[[本-古里安国际机场|本-古里安国际机场]]）執行的[[恐怖襲擊|恐怖襲擊]]事件，造成28人罹難與80人受傷（包括恐怖份子）<ref>"In what became known as the Lod Airport Massacre three members of the terrorist group, Japanese Red Army, arrived at the airport aboard Air France Flight 132 from Rome. Once inside the airport they grabbed automatic firearms from their carry-on cases and fired at airport staff and visitors. In the end, 26 people died and 80 people were injured." ''[[CBC_News|CBC News]]'', ''[[The_Fifth_Estate|The Fifth Estate]]'', "Fasten Your Seatbelts: Ben Gurion Airport in Israel", 2007. Accessed June 2, 2008.</ref>。

這次襲擊事件主要是由[[巴勒斯坦人|巴勒斯坦人]]先突襲[[機場安檢|機場安檢]]，並由日本赤軍協助。該事件常被形容是一個[[自殺攻擊|自殺攻擊]]，不過也有人聲稱，事件背後還有更大的[[陰謀論|陰謀]]，但此說法至今尚未獲得證實。<ref>[http://neojaponisme.com/2007/09/13/steinhoffpartfour/ Interview: Dr. Patricia Steinhoff 4] {{Wayback|url=http://neojaponisme.com/2007/09/13/steinhoffpartfour/ |date=20210501034317 }} ''Neojaponisme'', September 13, 2007. Accessed March 22, 2009.</ref>

